<subSubSection pageId="248" pageNumber="527" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6708207" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6708207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6708207/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="527" targetBox="[179,770,1995,2409]" targetPageId="248">
<paragraph blockId="248.[794,1388,1996,2415]" pageId="248" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,970,2224,2257]" pageId="248" pageNumber="527">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the type locality in NE Chile.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="248" pageNumber="527" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="248.[794,1388,1996,2415]" pageId="248" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,1079,2303,2336]" pageId="248" pageNumber="527">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 84-135 mm, tail 80-110 mm, ear 20-28 mm, hindfoot 24-29 mm; weight 27-57-5 g.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="248.[180,1386,2421,2887]" pageId="248" pageNumber="527">Osgood’s Leaf-eared Mouse is small, with buffy brown dorsum and pale neutral gray venter. Tail is equal to head-body length, auditory bullae are of regularsize, and interorbital region is posteriorly extended. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 40, FN = 72.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
